   <refnamediv>
       <refname>gamm_rnd </refname>
               <refpurpose>Gamma random draws </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>[gb]=gamm_rnd(nrow,ncol,m,k)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> nrow,ncol </term> =    the size of the matrix drawn</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> m </term> =    a parameter such that the mean of the gamma  =    m/k</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> k </term> =    a parameter such that the variance of the gamma  =    m/(k^2)</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> r </term> =    an nrow x ncol matrix of random numbers from the gamma distribution</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Performs a matrix of random draws from the gamma distribution.
  REFERENCE: Luc Devroye, Non-Uniform Random Variate Generation, New York: Springer Verlag, 1986, ch 9.3-6.
  Note: m=r/2, k=2 equals chisq r random deviate.
 
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
x=gamm_rnd(5,4,3,3)
 
               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>AUTHOR</title>
Eric Dubois 2002
        </refsection>
</refentry>
